aa(lp288
VNow in some cases, the search for bodies
p289
aVthat could push athletic performance forward
p290
aVended up introducing into the competitive world
p291
aVpopulations of people that weren't previously competing at all,
p292
aVlike Kenyan distance runners.
p293
aVWe think of Kenyans as being great marathoners.
p294
aVKenyans think of the Kalenjin tribe
p295
aVas being great marathoners.
p296
aVThe Kalenjin make up just 12 percent
p297
aVof the Kenyan population
p298
aVbut the vast majority of elite runners.
p299
aVAnd they happen, on average,
p300
aVto have a certain unique physiology:
p301
aVlegs that are very long
p302
aVand very thin at their extremity,
p303
aVand this is because they have their ancestry
p304
aVat very low latitude
p305
aVin a very hot and dry climate,
p306
