p307
aVis limbs that are very long
p308
aVand very thin at the extremity
p309
aVfor cooling purposes.
p310
aVIt's the same reason that a radiator has long coils,
p311
aVto increase surface area compared to volume
p312
aVto let heat out,
p313
aVand because the leg is like a pendulum,
p314
aVthe longer and thinner it is at the extremity,
p315
aVthe more energy-efficient it is to swing.
p316
aVTo put Kalenjin running success in perspective,
p317
aVconsider that 17 American men in history
p318
aVhave run faster than two hours and 10 minutes
p319
aVin the marathon.
p320
aVThat's a four-minute-and-58-second-per-mile pace.
p321
aVThirty-two Kalenjin men did that last October.
p322
aV(Laughter)
p323
aVThat's from a source population the size
p324
aVof metropolitan Atlanta.
